## Updating Coordination State

When you detect an issue, add it to the issue queue:

```json
{
  "issueQueue": [
    {
      "id": "issue-001",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-20T12:00:00Z",
      "severity": "error",
      "step": "implementation",
      "summary": "Build failed with 3 clippy errors",
      "details": "Missing lifetime annotations in handler.rs",
      "diagnostics": {
        "files": ["src/handler.rs"],
        "errors": ["error[E0106]: missing lifetime specifier"],
        "recommendation": "Add lifetime annotations or use owned types"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Severity Levels

| Severity | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `critical` | Blocking, needs immediate attention | Build completely broken |
| `error` | Significant issue affecting progress | Test failures |
| `warning` | Potential problem | Clippy warnings |
| `info` | Informational | Progress update |

